    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1252"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/392.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Bevan</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Several American firms were notified verbally this morning that war contributions
                    would have to be paid within twenty-four hours. Nafarrate is out of town and
                    subordinate is in Chargé. Subordinate agrees not to take any action until return
                    of Nafarrate tomorrow. Same discriminatory list is being used. Spanish firms
                    that have already made payments have been ordered to pay again double what they
                    paid first time. American firms will likewise have no guarantee against same
                    treatment should they make any payments. Bather than pay companies will close up
                    and have requested that consular seal placed on their doors. Respectfully
                    request instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bevan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
